intro : "<p>In this digital age, or even, the age after printing is invented by Johannes Gutenberg in 1440, it is incredibly easy to acquire books due to the cheap cost and the technological advancement that has occured in the world. Books are something you can find in abundance, and I'm willing to bet if you look around your house right now, you will find at least ONE book lying somewhere.</p>

<p>But then, before all this convenience existed, have you ever wondered how does people read books?</p>
        
<p>In an era without printing press, without paper, without any means to commercially produce books in such way that it is available to everyone?</p>
        
<p><i>Ascendance of a Bookworm</i>, the light novel series written by Miya Kazuki and illustrated by You Shiina, aims to explore the answer to that question.</p>"
